        <div class="formSection">
            <strong>Editorial Policy</strong>
            <p>
                The Mountainhome Herald is committed to accurate, timely, and impartial reporting on all matters
                affecting the citizens of the Grand Duchy of Eldoria. The Herald operates independently of the
                Arcane Council, the Grand Duke's office, and all registered guilds and commercial entities.
            </p>
            <p>
                All articles are subject to review by the Editor-in-Chief prior to publication. Corrections are
                published in the following edition. Letters to the Editor must be submitted in Dwarven Standard Script
                and are subject to length restrictions (maximum 200 runes). The Herald does not publish anonymous
                submissions from goblin sources.
            </p>
            <p>
                The Herald accepts no advertising from entities currently under indictment by the Fortress Guard,
                nor from known associates of the Undead Commerce League. Sponsored content, where it appears,
                is clearly marked with the designation "PAID STONE."
            </p>
        </div>

